steps.description:
If you love to talk and think all things food, find your bliss when shopping food and end up more often than not at the farmers market to do your food shopping, then you're the perfect candidate to start a cooking club. If you love talking about food with others, and enjoy all the nuances and specifics about special food products, a cooking club will provide you with the outlet to share this love with people who have the exact same passion. No more need to talk endlessly about the intricacies of food to a bewildered spouse or family member; use the club to get this out of your system! {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a6/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a6/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

If your cookbook collection has its very own bookshelf and is bulging at the seams, it's time to get the books down and start cooking those recipes with fellow foodies! {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f7/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f7/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Ask yourself what you want to get out of the club. Do you want to save money, make new friends, discover new cuisines, share recipes, etc.? You may have various motivators, and it's important to recognize these up front, so that you can begin tailoring the club toward this end and attract like-minded members. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9a/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/9a/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-1Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

You may wish to have the first meeting at your house, if you feel it's safe enough to do so. It's always advisable to have other people you know and trust around when you first meet the new club members. If you're not sure about bringing them into your home to begin with, hold the first meeting at a local cafe, bar or restaurant–-anywhere you can share and critique food together. After the club is established, the idea is to use your home kitchens and dining areas, once the trust is in place. At the first meeting, discuss meeting dates. Use an online calendar with reminder notices to help keep track of the cooking club dates. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/57/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/57/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Try to aim for a regular monthly date. It's important to realize that not all members will manage to make every meeting––build that reality into the flexibility of your meetups. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1c/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1c/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

There are lots of possible ways to run the "cooking" part of a cooking club, and it's something that you'll need to discuss together and reach a consensus on. Nothing is set in stone and no exact way is right over any other. Some suggestions include:

Theme cooking: Choose a theme that you are all interested in learning more about, such as national country-specific cooking (French, Greek, Chinese, etc. ); party cooking; baking; candy-making, etc. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/61\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/6\/61\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet1.jpg\/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Try-something-new cooking: Have club members come with a dish from a cuisine they've never attempted before. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/f8\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/f8\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet2.jpg\/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Cooking together: Instead of bringing a dish, bring a recipe and have everyone pitch in together to make the recipes for a whole meal. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0c\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet3.jpg\/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/0\/0c\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet3.jpg\/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Freezer-friendly cook-up: You get to cook one meal in enough quantities for, say 4 club members, share this meal with the others and keep their additional meals to place in your freezer for the upcoming month! For those who like the idea of freeze-ahead meals but lack the motivation, a club can help get you right into this time-saving measure. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/9\/9b\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet4.jpg\/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/9\/9b\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet4.jpg\/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Budget cooking: A cooking club can be a fantastic way to pool resources to pay for more expensive food items. {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/f2\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet5.jpg\/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/f\/f2\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet5.jpg\/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Making preserves: Preserves (jams, jellies, chutneys, vinegar- and oil-preserved food, etc.) are wonderful to have in the pantry but finding the motivation and adequate knowledge to make them alone can feel daunting. As part of a club, you can share lots of ideas, have many helping hands and each of you take home a jar or more after each club session! {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/eb\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet6.jpg\/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/e\/eb\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet6.jpg\/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Deconstructed store food: For those lacking in time, hold sessions where you're perfectly allowed to build on bought food and try to improve on it, rather than cooking from scratch. Even if this isn't your usual theme, this can be a good one for busier times (such as holiday season) or when lots of members are away (summer vacation time). {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/15\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet7.jpg\/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet7.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/1\/15\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet7.jpg\/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet7.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Parents/carers and kids cook-up: Teach your kids how to cook in a group situation––this can be great for sharing ideas around and keeping your patience intact while the mess gets cleaned up by everyone involved! {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/71\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet8.jpg\/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet8.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/7\/71\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet8.jpg\/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet8.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}


Book club-meets-cooking club: An occasional read of a book about food––chef's, restaurateur's and foodie travelers' experiences, etc. all qualify for good food reads; some cookbooks might be okay if they contain enough interest beyond a mere assembly of recipes. Have a chat about how you found the book, then head off to cook something inspired by the reading! {"smallUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/8b\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet9.jpg\/v4-460px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet9.jpg","bigUrl":"https:\/\/www.wikihow.com\/images\/thumb\/8\/8b\/Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet9.jpg\/v4-760px-Start-a-Cooking-Club-Step-4Bullet9.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>License: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https:\/\/creativecommons.org\/licenses\/by-nc-sa\/3.0\/\">Creative Commons<\/a><br>\n<\/p><p><br \/>\n<\/p><\/div>"}

